description: Displaced Kashmiri Pandits voted with a unified demand for a 'homeland' in Kashmir after 36 years of exile. They criticized government job and housing proposals as mere symbols. Despite boycott calls, many participated in elections, emphasizing sustainable job opportunities to ensure their community's permanent return and preserve their ancient civilization.
title: Pandit elders seek a 'homeland', youth eye opportunities

description: Sandeep Paswan, a 33-year-old chartered accountant from Jharkhand, allegedly took his own life at his rented Govandi home after accusing his fiancee and her family of framing him in a stalking case and assaulting him. He also alleged that police refused to intervene in the financial dispute, leading him to seek court intervention.
title: CA says fiancee, kin framed him in stalking case after taking Rs 12L, kills self on FB Live

description: TISS has lifted its ban on the Progressive Students' Forum and revised its honour code to eliminate a controversial pledge against political activities. This decision came after thorough deliberations by the institute's authority, aiming to preserve mutual respect and academic integrity. PSF welcomed this change, advocating for students' right to free speech.
title: TISS revokes its ban on student outfit, tweaks 'honour code'

description: Sameer Khan, son-in-law of NCP functionary Nawab Malik, suffered severe injuries including a brain clot when his driver accidentally accelerated and crashed into him outside a Kurla hospital. The incident occurred as the driver mistook the accelerator for the brake. Khan is now in ICU under observation for 48 hours.
title: Driver crashes SUV into Nawab Malik's son-in-law

description: EY Restructuring has resigned from advising Pankaj Srivastava, the NCLT-appointed internal resolution professional at Byju's. This development follows BDO’s resignation as Byju’s auditor earlier this month. Srivastava is currently inviting lenders, employees, vendors, and government entities to claim unpaid dues. Representatives from the IRP, EY, and Byju’s have not responded to queries.
title: EY resigns as adviser to Byju's IRP

description: Chief of Defence Staff General Anil Chauhan emphasized India's need to prepare for both short and long-duration conflicts amid ongoing tensions with China in eastern Ladakh. He highlighted the focus on operational preparedness, modernization, transformation, and indigenization as key pillars for national security. He also noted a global trend towards increased defense spending due to rising insecurity.
title: India a 'vishwa mitra', but must be prepared for conflicts: CDS

description: Congress has filed a complaint with Delhi Police over recent statements by NDA leaders targeting Rahul Gandhi. The party claims these remarks, including assassination threats and derogatory comments, are intended to jeopardize his safety and disturb public peace ahead of the J&K and Haryana elections. They demand an FIR against the individuals involved.
title: Congress files police plaint over NDA netas' threats against Rahul Gandhi

description: Engineer Rashid of Awami Ittehad Party has emerged as a pivotal figure in Kashmir's elections after being released from jail. Accusations swirl about his alleged role as a BJP proxy, challenging traditional parties like PDP and NC. His influence could significantly shape the election results on October 8.
title: With bail stirring suspicion, all eyes on Engineer's impact

description: Congress has unveiled seven guarantees for Haryana before the assembly elections, including a caste census and legal guarantee for minimum support price. Other pledges include free electricity up to 300 units, Rs 2,000 monthly for women aged 18-60, and reinstating the Old Pension Scheme. The state will vote on October 5.
title: Caste census, MSP legal shield, OPS & more: Congress unveils '7Gs'

description: In Chennai, J Pavithran, a 19-year-old food delivery executive and Bcom student, took his own life after being scolded by a woman customer for late grocery delivery. He left a note expressing his dejection. Police are investigating the incident and any actions taken by the delivery company following the customer's complaint.
title: Told off by customer, delivery boy kills self

description: Seventy-two of the top 100 JEE (Advanced) rankers have opted for IIT Bombay, with all top 10 choosing computer science there. IIT Delhi follows with 23 students, and IIT Madras has two. The data underscores IIT Bombay's status as a leading choice for quality engineering education among top performers.
title: 72 in top 100 & all in top 10 AIR pick IIT Bombay
19-year-old dies by suicide in Kota; cops order probe

description: Shankar Das, pro-vice-chancellor at Tata Institute of Social Sciences, will serve as interim vice-chancellor for Gokhale Institute of Politics and Economics starting September 22. This follows the refusal by the senior-most professor to assume the role after Ajit Ranade was removed due to not meeting eligibility criteria related to teaching experience.
title: TISS pro-VC to be interim head of Gokhale Institute

description: The Union Cabinet has approved the establishment of the National Centre of Excellence for animation, visual effects, gaming, comics and extended reality in Mumbai. This initiative aims to make India a global hub for content creation by providing specialized training and fostering research. It also seeks to boost employment and attract foreign investments into the media and entertainment sector.
title: Institute to be set up in Mumbai to boost AVGC-XR industry

description: The Union Cabinet has approved the Pradhan Mantri Janjatiya Unnat Gram Abhiyan aimed at improving the socio-economic conditions of tribal communities. The scheme will cover approximately 63,000 villages and benefit more than 5 crore tribal people with a total outlay of Rs 79,156 crore. It includes various interventions by 17 ministries over five years.
title: Rs 79,000cr scheme to benefit 5cr tribals in 63,000 villages

description: A tourist's photo showing plant growth on the Taj Mahal's central dome has raised concerns about its maintenance. Despite the Archaeological Survey of India's annual Rs 4 crore preservation budget, recent rainwater seepage and structural issues have sparked criticism. Calls for immediate conservation efforts have intensified following these developments.
title: Plant sprouting from Taj's dome sparks worries over upkeep

description: The Union cabinet has sanctioned India's fourth Moon mission, Chandrayaan-4, focused on returning lunar samples to Earth. It also approved constructing Bharatiya Antariksh Station by 2028 and completing it by 2035. Additionally, approvals were granted for the Venus Orbiter Mission and a reusable next-generation launch vehicle with enhanced payload capacity.
title: 4 key space projects receive the go-ahead from Cabinet

description: Two Chhattisgarh Armed Force jawans lost their lives and two others were injured when a fellow jawan opened fire at them in Balrampur district. The shooting happened at Bhutahi camp after an argument over missing meal items. The accused, Ajay Sidar, has been detained by the police.
title: 'Something missing in meals', cop shoots dead 2 jawans at Chhattisgarh camp

description: Union home and cooperation minister Amit Shah is set to launch initiatives aimed at strengthening India's cooperative movement, including White Revolution 2.0 to transform the dairy sector and SOPs for a 'cooperation among cooperatives' campaign. The goal is to boost milk procurement by 50% over five years and support new cooperative societies in uncovered regions.
title: Amit Shah to launch today 'White Revolution 2.0', new SOPs for co-ops

description: The government announced partial restoration of wheat allocation under the Pradhan Mantri Gareeb Kalyan Ann Yojana, increasing supply to 220 lakh tonnes annually. Beneficiaries in states like Uttar Pradesh and Gujarat will benefit. Additionally, a Rs 1,000 crore credit guarantee scheme for banks has been approved to support farmers and traders with loans against electronic Negotiable Warehouse Receipts.
title: More rotis in poors' plate as govt partially restores wheat allocation

description: India abstained from voting on a UN General Assembly resolution calling for Israel to end its presence in the Occupied Palestinian Territory within 12 months. The resolution was adopted with strong support: 124 votes in favor, 14 against, and 43 abstentions. It criticizes Israel's violations of international law and their impact on regional peace.
title: India skips vote on UNGA call for end to Israeli occupation

description: NASA plans to launch the Europa Clipper mission on October 10, 2024, targeting Jupiter’s icy moon Europa. The mission seeks to explore whether Europa’s subsurface ocean can harbor life. The spacecraft will execute 49 flybys of the moon to gather crucial data about its ice shell and potential habitability while navigating intense radiation zones.
title: Europa Clipper mission set to explore Jupiter’s ocean moon; all you need to know

description: Gurpatwant Singh Pannun of Sikhs for Justice has filed a civil lawsuit against the Indian government and key officials in a US court. He seeks compensation for an alleged assassination attempt on him last year. The plot, involving high-ranking Indian officials, was foiled by undercover US agents. Pannun claims ongoing threats to his life.
title: Pannun files civil lawsuit in US against GOI, Doval and others, seeks damages

description: The initial phase of the J&K assembly elections witnessed a voter turnout of 59% across 24 constituencies under tight security. This turnout is higher than in previous years, showing increased voter participation. The subsequent phases are set for Sept 25 and Oct 1, with final results expected on Oct 8.
title: 59% turnout in first phase of J&K assembly polls

description: BJP has suspended three rebels, Pawan Khajuria, Balwan Singh, and Narinder Singh Bhau, for contesting against its official candidates in the ongoing J&K assembly polls. The suspension was ordered by BJP’s J&K working president Sat Paul Sharma on recommendations from the party’s disciplinary committee chaired by Sunil Sethi.
title: BJP suspends 3 rebels in J&K for contesting against party candidates

description: The United States reaffirms its long-standing opposition to supporting Pakistan's ballistic missile program, emphasizing continued enforcement of sanctions for national security. Recent US sanctions targeted a Chinese research institute and companies for allegedly supplying missile-related items to Pakistan. In response, Pakistan criticized the actions as biased and politically motivated.
title: US intensifies criticism of Pak ballistic missile programme

description: Andhra Pradesh CM N Chandrababu Naidu accused the previous YSRCP government of mixing animal fat in the ghee used for Tirumala laddu, leading to controversy. He criticized the quality of materials and stated that the NDA government is taking measures to restore temple sanctity. YSRCP denied these allegations.
title: During Jagan's term, Tirumala laddu had animal fat: Chandrababu Naidu

description: The government has approved the continuation of PM-Aasha and a subsidy on phosphatic and potassic fertilisers for the upcoming rabi season of 2024-25, with an outlay of nearly Rs 60,000 crore. This move aims to ensure minimum support prices for farmers and provide affordable crop nutrients.
title: Govt extends Rs 35,000cr plan to boost income of farmers

description: The US Federal Reserve has lowered interest rates by 50 basis points, marking its first cut in over four years. This action is likely to increase foreign investment in India, influence the Indian Rupee, and benefit sectors like IT and consumer goods. The RBI's response will be key to maintaining financial stability.
title: US Fed cuts interest rates by 50 bps in a first since 2020: Why it matters for India

description: A wave of mysterious device explosions in Lebanon has left nine dead and over 300 injured. These incidents come after a similar attack on Hezbollah members, blamed on Israel. The explosions have intensified regional tensions, raising concerns about potential conflict escalation.
title: Video: Moment walkie-talkies exploded across Lebanon during funeral

description: US Federal Reserve Meeting: The US Federal Reserve has cut interest rates by 50 basis points, the first reduction in over four years, aiming to reverse restrictive economic conditions. Policymakers expect further rate cuts, targeting a range of 4.25%-4.50% by year-end as inflation nears the 2% goal and unemployment rises.
title: US Federal Reserve cuts interest rates by 50 bps in key FOMC meet chaired by Jerome Powell

description: A Shanghai court has mandated that a dog owner compensate a woman with 90,000 yuan after she miscarried due to being startled by his unleashed golden retriever. The woman had endured multiple IVF treatments over three years. The court held the dog owner accountable for the emotional and physical distress inflicted.
title: China man pays compensation to woman after she suffers miscarriage

description: Coldplay has announced they will return to India in 2025 as part of their Music of the Spheres World Tour. This marks their first solo performance in India since appearing at the Global Citizen Festival in Mumbai in 2016. Specific dates and venue details have not yet been revealed, but fans are already excited.
title: Coldplay confirms return to India in 2025

description: The friction between Nia Jax and Rhea Ripley continues to grow. During a WWE live event, Ripley countered Jax's stinkface move, creating a viral moment. Jax felt disrespected by this action and accused Ripley of trying to steal the spotlight. Currently, Jax holds the Queen of the Ring title and is in her second reign as WWE Women’s Champion.
title: Nia Jax reveals she felt disrespected by Rhea Ripley
MAGA mom mocks Kamala for not having biological children

description: Delhi Police have issued a warning to fans of Diljit Dosanjh regarding online ticket scams for his upcoming Dil-Luminati Tour 2024. A Delhi woman reported losing Rs 15,000 to a scammer who provided fake identity proof.
title: Diljit Dosanjh tour: Here’s ticket scam warning with screenshots

description: Former Pakistan cricketer Basit Ali criticized Australian spinner Nathan Lyon's bold prediction of a 5-0 victory for Australia in the upcoming Border-Gavaskar Trophy series against India. Ali suggested such claims are better suited to former players. Australian batsman Travis Head acknowledged the challenge of facing India, noting their competitive nature. The series starts on November 22 in Perth.
title: 'Stupid': Basit blasts Aus bowler for 5-0 win prediction over India

description: The Indian Premier League Auction for Season 18 is expected to be held in November, possibly in the Middle East. Franchises are concerned about the delay in retention rules, which may be announced by month-end. Former Indian team coaches under Rahul Dravid are likely to join various IPL franchises this season.
title: IPL 2025 auction likely to be held outside India in November

description: India has asked Pakistan to review the 1960 Indus Waters Treaty, highlighting issues such as cross-border terrorism and environmental concerns. This follows recent terror attacks and disputes over hydroelectric projects. India seeks a reassessment of treaty obligations due to significant changes in circumstances, including population demographics and clean energy needs.
title: Citing cross-border terrorism, India seeks Indus treaty review
Top-notch drone goes down off Chennai ahead of mega US deal

description: Sana Khan discussed her transition from the entertainment industry to a spiritual life on Rubina Dilaik’s podcast. She expressed guilt over her past choices and how they conflicted with her Muslim beliefs. Despite material success, she felt unfulfilled. In 2020, she left acting, got married later that year, and welcomed motherhood in 2023.
title: Bigg Boss fame Sana Khan breaks down in tears, regretting old days

description: Jordan Chiles might keep her Olympic bronze medal thanks to footage from Simone Biles’ Netflix documentary. The video indicates that Chiles’ appeal was submitted on time, disputing the Court of Arbitration for Sport’s decision. This new evidence could potentially reinstate Chiles’ medal position, which had been awarded to Romania’s Ana Barbosu.
title: Biles' documentary footage may hold crucial evidence in Chiles' medal appeal

description: On Wednesday, explosions linked to walkie-talkies used by Hezbollah struck Lebanon's southern regions and Beirut's suburbs, causing numerous casualties and injuries. Thousands of explosive-rigged pagers detonated simultaneously. In response, Hezbollah launched rocket strikes on Israeli artillery positions, escalating tensions in the region.
title: What is a walkie-talkie? Device linked to round 2 of fatal blasts in Lebanon

description: It’s a sentiment that a lot of political watchers can probably sympathise with, as the name Sean “Diddy” Combs suddenly dominates the MAGA vs KHive conversation. What exactly is a Sean Combs? Is his name Diddy? And why is he suddenly in the news? How is he connected to Obama, Harris and Trump?
title: How is Diddy connected to Obama and Trump?

description: Donald Trump claimed that Prime Minister Narendra Modi will visit the US to meet him next week. PM Modi's official schedule includes attending the Quad summit hosted by President Biden and other events in New York City, but no meeting with Trump is listed. The Indian Embassy and State Department have not commented on Trump's claim.
title: Trump claims 'fantastic' Modi is coming to US to meet him

description: The Union Cabinet has approved four key space missions and doubled the budget for Gaganyaan, India’s first human spaceflight mission. The new missions include Chandrayaan-4, Venus Orbiter Mission, Next Generation Launch Vehicle, and Bhartiya Antriksh Station. These initiatives aim to advance India’s capabilities in space exploration and establish its global presence.
title: Moon, Mars, Sun and now Venus: Union cabinet gives big boost to Isro

description: The initial phase of Jammu and Kashmir's assembly elections concluded with a voter turnout of 58.85 per cent, with Kishtwar leading at 77 per cent and Pulwama trailing at just over 46 per cent. This election is significant as it is the first since Article 370 was revoked.
title: J&K polls: Phase 1 concludes with over 58% voter turnout, lower from 2014
'One nation, one election': How Lok Sabha and assembly polls could be synchronised

description: The Union Cabinet chaired by Prime Minister Narendra Modi has approved significant initiatives like the 'one nation, one election' framework to synchronize elections across India. Other approvals include the Chandrayaan-4 lunar mission, subsidies for P&K fertilizers for the rabi season, and extending the PM-AASHA scheme. A program aimed at uplifting tribal communities was also sanctioned.
title: Union Cabinet meeting: One nation, one election, lunar exploration & key decisions

description: A Japanese man harassed his wife with 100 silent calls daily for a month due to jealousy. The woman from Hyogo prefecture reported it to the police after suspecting her husband's involvement. Police confirmed he was behind the calls, leading to his arrest. This incident has sparked discussions on relationship communication and controlling behavior.
title: Japan: 'Jealous' husband arrested after making over 100 calls every day

description: The NFL has experienced several shocking moments over the years, including suspensions for gambling involving Paul Hornung and Alex Karras, O.J. Simpson's high-profile murder trial, and Chuck Hughes' tragic on-field death. The article also highlights the Patriots' unexpected Super Bowl XXXVI victory, showcasing the sport's intense and unpredictable nature.

description: Singer and actor Diljit Dosanjh's honest revelations provide insight into his journey from Punjab to global fame. He shares his childhood prayers for recognition, challenges with English, initial skepticism about Bollywood offers, and an unwavering bond with Punjab. Further, Diljit's joy at receiving a Madame Tussauds statue reflects his authenticity.
title: Diljit Dosanjh’s 5 most honest confessions proving he is like us

description: India have historically dominated Test cricket against Bangladesh, winning 11 out of 13 matches. Former cricketer Mohammad Kaif believes that despite Bangladesh's recent success against Pakistan, it will be tough for them to beat India at home. The series will feature strong spinners from both sides and begins in Chennai on Thursday.
title: Exclusive: 'Bangladesh played very well in Pakistan, but India…'

description: Rishabh Pant makes his Test cricket comeback after two years against Bangladesh at Chennai's MA Chidambaram Stadium. Despite Dhruv Jurel's impressive form, Team India's head coach Gautam Gambhir stresses Pant's crucial role as a batter and wicketkeeper. Recent domestic matches have proven Pant’s readiness for the challenges of red-ball cricket.
title: Rishabh Pant set for Test return after 632 days

description: A 38-year-old man from Kerala's Malappuram has been diagnosed with monkeypox after returning from Dubai. He self-isolated upon noticing symptoms and is now undergoing treatment. This comes after a recent case in Delhi, making it the 30th reported instance of monkeypox in India since July 2022, as per the Union health ministry.
title: Monkeypox in India: Second case of Mpox confirmed in Kerala

description: The Union Cabinet has approved the 'one nation, one election' proposal recommended by a panel led by former president Ram Nath Kovind. Opposition parties criticize the move as impractical and harmful to federalism. Meanwhile, BJP and its allies support it, citing benefits like reduced election expenses and improved law and order.
title: 'One nation, one poll': PM says 'important for vibrant democracy'; Oppn dubs it 'impractical'

description: Cody Rhodes and Roman Reigns join forces to battle Solo Sikoa and Jacob Fatu at 'Bad Blood' on SmackDown. There could be some massive shocks on offer like Jimmy Uso's return, Hikuleo's debut, and a possible betrayal by Jacob Fatu. The match promises intense drama and excitement for wrestling fans.
title: 3 twists that could happen in Cody Rhodes/Roman Reigns vs Bloodline 2.0 match

description: Vivek Ramaswamy said neither the residents of Springfield nor the immigrants should be blamed for the situation in Springfield. The community in Springfield was not prepared to handle the pressure of the immigrants who have been allowed to settle there by 'awful federal policies', Vivek said as Ohio's Springfield continues to seethe amid rumors of 'eating cats' and several bomb threats.
title: Ramaswamy explains who's to blame for 'Haitian immigrants eating cats' row

description: Anip Patel, CEO of CaPatel Investments, criticized Air India after a non-stop flight from Chicago to Delhi. He described it as a nightmare due to unclean cabins, broken entertainment systems, and unavailable food items. Despite new management's promises of better service, his expectations were unmet.
title: Watch: Indian-American CEO shares 'worst' Air India experience

description: Gold Apollo, a Taiwanese pager manufacturer, has denied involvement in producing devices used in Lebanon explosions. The company stated that its European licensee, BAC, was responsible for manufacturing the pagers. Gold Apollo plans to sue BAC for damages and maintains it is a victim of the incident.
title: Gold Apollo accused of making pagers used in Lebanon blasts: We are small, but ...

description: Arvind Kejriwal, the outgoing chief minister of Delhi, has announced he will give up all government facilities and vacate his official residence within 15 days. He aims to live like a common man without security or official vehicles. Concerns for his safety have been raised due to past attacks.
title: Kejriwal to vacate CM residence, give up security to live as 'common man': AAP

description: Abdu Rozik, a former Bigg Boss 16 contestant, has called off his wedding with Amira citing cultural differences. He stressed the need for a mentally resilient partner and expressed gratitude for his supporters' unwavering support. Abdu remains hopeful about finding love again and continues to inspire his followers with his positive outlook.
title: Bigg Boss 16 fame Abdu Rozik calls off wedding with fiancée Amira

description: The Indian government has sanctioned a Rs 31,000 crore project to fence the entire 1,643 km India-Myanmar border to address smuggling issues. This measure impacts Manipur, Mizoram, Nagaland, and Arunachal Pradesh. Union Home Minister Amit Shah stated that 30 km of fencing is done. The Free Movement Regime has been terminated.
title: Govt to spend Rs 31,000 crore to fence 1,643 km India-Myanmar border

description: Andy Tomkins and his team at Monash University propose that Earth once had rings lasting ten million years, affecting its climate. Their analysis of asteroid craters from 466 million years ago suggests a debris ring formed from an asteroid's fragmentation, which may have contributed to a global cooling event during that period.
title: Study reveals Earth once had rings similar to Saturn's; find more

description: Wrestler-turned-politician Vinesh Phogat has joined Congress and criticized the BJP government for issues like unemployment and lack of respect for Haryana's people. Urging voters to support Congress in the October 5 elections, she promised a symbolic 'slap' to the current administration. Phogat is running from Julana Assembly constituency against BJP's Captain Yogesh Bairagi.
title: 'Symbol of hand will act as slap': Vinesh Phogat takes aim at BJP

description: New Zealand withdrew from their limited-overs series in Pakistan minutes before the first ODI due to a credible security threat. Despite extensive security measures by Pakistan, New Zealand prioritized player safety after consulting with officials and their government. This unexpected move affects Pakistan's efforts to host international cricket and future tour prospects.
title: Security threat! When NZ called off Pakistan tour

description: Newly appointed head coach Gautam Gambhir highlights the importance of maintaining good relationships with senior players like Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli to take Indian cricket forward. Gambhir also emphasizes clear communication in selecting the playing eleven and underscores the significance of bench strength, ensuring players are ready for future opportunities.
title: 'It's still early days, but...': Gambhir on relationship with seniors

description: The Union Cabinet has approved expansions in India's space exploration programs such as Chandrayaan-4, Gaganyaan follow-up missions, and the Venus Orbiter Mission. Chandrayaan-4 will include two spacecraft stacks for lunar sample collection and return. This mission aims to advance India's space capabilities using upgraded LVM-3 rockets.
title: Govt approves Chandrayaan-4 expansion with Rs 2,104cr allocation

description: India has formally notified Pakistan, seeking amendments to the Indus Water Treaty due to significant changes in circumstances and lack of cooperation from Pakistan. The treaty, established in 1960, allocates waters from eastern rivers to India and western rivers to Pakistan. Disputes continue over India's efforts to utilize its allotted water resources.
title: Indus Water Treaty: India serves formal notice to Pak, seeks modification

description: Tonight's full moon is set to be a supermoon, appearing larger and brighter than usual. Best viewing times are around 6pm in Sydney and Melbourne, 7pm in London and New York, and 7:30pm on the US West Coast. A partial lunar eclipse will occur but won't be visible from Australia.
title: September 18 Supermoon: When and where to see it

description: The article discusses high-profile marriages between Indian cricketers and Bollywood actresses. It features couples like Virat Kohli with Anushka Sharma, Yuvraj Singh with Hazel Keech, Harbhajan Singh with Geeta Basra, Zaheer Khan with Sagarika Ghatge, and Mansoor Ali Khan Pataudi with Sharmila Tagore. These unions combine cricketing excellence with cinematic allure.
title: Top Cricket-Bollywood couples: Virat-Anushka to Zaheer-Sagarika

description: Police in Guna district, Madhya Pradesh, solved the Hanuman temple robbery case by arresting a gang from Rajasthan. After a 20-day investigation, they used CCTV footage to track the robbers who had disguised themselves as women. Three people, including a jeweller, were arrested and stolen silver jewellery was recovered.
title: 'Undercover' cops crack temple heist, arrest robbers dressed as women

description: Yashasvi Jaiswal's remarkable performance in the World Test Championship cycle has captured attention. Scoring 712 runs in 9 innings against England, including a maiden double century, he now ranks second among leading run-scorers for the 2023-25 WTC season. His consistency and ability to score big have set him apart.
title: Yashasvi inches closer to overtaking this legend

description: AAP Rajya Sabha MP Swati Maliwal has intensified her criticism of Delhi minister Atishi, who was selected by outgoing CM Arvind Kejriwal as his successor. Maliwal alleges that Atishi's parents had connections with Syed Abdul Rahman Geelani, an accused in the 2001 Parliament attack. AAP leader Dilip Pandey has urged Maliwal to resign from her position.

description: Explosives embedded in over 5000 pagers by Mossad triggered simultaneous explosions across Lebanon, causing over 11 deaths and injuring more than 3000 people. Hezbollah blamed Israel for the attack and vowed retaliation. Taiwanese company Gold Apollo denied involvement, stating they only authorized the brand and had no part in designing or manufacturing the pagers.

description: India's Test and ODI captain Rohit Sharma is humorously known for his forgetfulness, as highlighted by teammates like Virat Kohli. The act became a social media sensation, generating positive reactions and memes praising Sunil's performance.
title: Archana Puran Singh compares Sunil Grover to Jim Carrey

Only two other Indians, Kapil Dev and Ravichandran Ashwin, have achieved this feat. Jadeja's chance comes in the upcoming series against Bangladesh.

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi is scheduled to visit the US from September 21 to 23 for the 4th Quad summit. Although an official meeting with Donald Trump is not listed, PM Modi will engage with key stakeholders in India-US relations. He will address both the Indian community and the United Nations General Assembly during his visit.

description: Rahul Gandhi urged Jammu and Kashmir residents to vote in the first phase of polling, supporting the INDIA bloc. He criticised the abrogation of Article 370 as a violation of constitutional rights. Gandhi emphasised that each vote for INDIA would help restore rights, create jobs, empower women, and end injustice in Jammu and Kashmir.
title: J&K polls: 'Will restore your rights', Rahul urges people to vote for INDIA bloc

The company will seek court approval to continue operations and initiate a sale process during the proceedings. Tupperware has faced declining sales and financial challenges, aiming to transform into a digital-first, technology-led firm.
title: Tupperware files for bankruptcy as company seeks 'strategic alternatives'

He attributed challenges like the Covid pandemic and limited time out of power to reduced productive years. Pawar also discussed potential constitutional changes and acknowledged his party's desire for him to become chief minister, emphasizing voter choice.
title: 'Discouraging': Ajit Pawar laments lack of credit for Baramati development

description: A series of pager explosions in Beirut's southern suburbs resulted in nine fatalities and over 2,700 injuries. Hezbollah attributes the blasts to explosives planted by Israel’s Mossad.

title: Chandigarh court issues notice to Kangana Ranaut over her film 'Emergency'

description: NPS Vatsalya launch today: Nirmala Sitharaman, Union Minister for Finance and Corporate Affairs, will launch the NPS Vatsalya scheme today. This initiative focuses on securing children's financial future through a pension account.
title: NPS Vatsalya: FM Sitaraman to launch new scheme today

description: Gautam Gambhir, India's head coach, downplayed worries about the team's performance against top spin bowlers before their Test series against Bangladesh. He praised India's strong batting lineup and highlighted their powerful bowling unit led by Jasprit Bumrah, Mohammed Shami, R Ashwin, and Ravindra Jadeja. Gambhir also commended Rishabh Pant's wicket-keeping skills in Indian conditions.
title: Gambhir dismisses concerns of quality' batting unit against spin

description: Tamil Nadu CM MK Stalin condemned threats against Rahul Gandhi, attributing them to his rising public support. Congress chief Mallikarjun Kharge called on PM Modi to discipline BJP leaders over their violent statements. Complaints were lodged against several BJP leaders for making threatening remarks towards Gandhi.
title: 'My brother's charisma unsettled many': DMK's Stalin on threats to Rahul

description: India's head coach Gautam Gambhir stressed the importance of a winning style before the Test series against Bangladesh. He praised senior players like R Ashwin and Ravindra Jadeja and addressed misconceptions about players prioritizing IPL over national duties. Gambhir expressed confidence in India's batting prowess against spin attacks.
title: Gambhir ahead of Bangladesh Tests: 'The winning style is the best style'

description: Pagers used by Hezbollah exploded across Lebanon, causing nine deaths and over 3000 injuries in what is suspected to be an operation by Israel's Mossad. Explosives were reportedly planted in the devices during production. This incident represents a major security breach for Hezbollah, which had adopted pagers to avoid Israeli surveillance.
title: Why was Hezbollah using outdated pagers in 2024?

description: Arvind Kejriwal will vacate his official residence within a week after resigning as Delhi's Chief Minister. Despite security concerns, he remains firm on his decision.  Atishi's name was also proposed at the Political Affairs Committee (PAC) meeting held at Arvind Kejriwal's residence last night. ​​Her name was proposed, and a consensus was agreed upon by party members.​​​​
title: 'Tried to make him understand ...': Kejriwal to move out of CM residence

description: The US FDA has awarded breakthrough device status to Neuralink's Blindsight, an experimental implant designed to restore vision. Developed by Elon Musk's company, the device aims to assist individuals who have lost their sight or were born blind. Initially offering low-resolution vision, it holds potential for future enhancements that may exceed natural sight.
title: Musk’s Neuralink sight implant gets FDA 'breakthrough' status. What is it

description: Lieutenant Governor V K Saxena announced the resumption of land mutation based on inheritance for agricultural land in over 174 urban villages in Delhi. The process begins with camps set up in villages starting Friday. This decision impacts lakhs of residents who were denied this right since 2010 due to urbanization.
title: Delhi LG: Mutation of land in urban villages open, move to benefit lakhs

description: Moo Deng, a month-old baby pygmy hippo born at Khao Kheow Open Zoo in Thailand, has captured global attention. Pygmy hippos are native to West Africa and are considered endangered due to habitat loss and hunting. The zoo has experienced a significant increase in visitors since her birth. Know more about Moo Deng.
title: Moo Deng, the baby hippo is internet's favorite child right now

description: Manu Bhaker from Haryana won two bronze medals at the Paris Olympics in women's and mixed 10 metre air pistol events. The 22-year-old is now aiming for gold at the Los Angeles Olympics. Supported by coach Jaspal Rana, her family, and teammates, Manu turned Tokyo's disappointment into motivation for her recent success.
title: My sights set on hitting the bullseye: Manu Bhaker

description: India's cricket team, led by Rohit Sharma, is focused on winning the World Test Championship (WTC) to complete their trophy collection. As part of the WTC cycle, they play a two-match Test series against Bangladesh. While India have historically dominated these encounters, Bangladesh enter the series with boosted morale following a historic win over Pakistan.
title: India vs Bangladesh: It's one-sided on paper, but what does the form guide say
Fired techie shares 'survival story' on LinkedIn, post viral
Mayoral debate spirals out of control after candidate throws chair at rival

description: Gautam Gambhir and Virat Kohli had a lighthearted discussion in an interview to be released by the BCCI, showing their improved rapport since Gambhir became Team India's head coach. The conversation took place ahead of the Test series against Bangladesh, with a teaser released on Wednesday. Both were part of India's 2011 ODI World Cup-winning team.
title: 'Putting an end to all the masala': Virat, Gambhir

description: Reliance Jio's 'Diwali Dhamaka' offer provides one year of free JioAirFiber service. Running from September 18 to November 3, it targets new customers spending Rs 20,000 or more at Reliance Digital or MyJio stores, or opting for a new JioAirFiber connection with a three-month Diwali plan priced at Rs 2,222.
title: Jio announced 'Diwali Dhamaka' offer with JioAirFiber free for one year: Details

description: A family in Ayodhya has offered a Rs 10,000 reward for information on their missing parrot named Mitthu. Known for mimicking human voices and greeting guests by name, the bird flew away when its cage was mistakenly left open. The family is very worried and hopes to find their beloved pet soon.
title: 'Well trained': UP man offers Rs 10,000 reward for info on missing parrot

description: Junior doctors in Bengal remain on strike, seeking more visible safety and security measures before resuming duties. A meeting with the chief secretary is anticipated to address these concerns. Despite the CM's appeal for them to return, doctors await further assurances.
title: 'Want more visible action': Kolkata junior doctors say not ending stir yet

description: Gangster 'Kakkathope' Balaji, involved in over 40 criminal cases including extortion and murder, was killed by police near Vyasarpadi Jeeva railway station. When police tried to arrest him, he attacked them, prompting officers to open fire. Balaji was declared dead at Government Stanley Hospital. He had significant control over parts of north Chennai.
title: Gangster 'Kakkathope' Balaji killed in police encounter in Tamil Nadu

description: Rohit Sharma addresses the continuous pressure on India's cricket team even after their World Cup triumph. As they prepare for a Test series against Bangladesh, he underscores the necessity of focus and adaptability with new coach Gautam Gambhir. The team's objective is to secure consistent victories and aim for the WTC Final.
title: Why the pressure is back on Rohit Sharma and Team India

description: Anjali Tatrari shares her experiences playing Yuvika in Vanshaj as the show concludes. She discusses learning resilience from her character and highlights emotional scenes as her strength. Anjali expresses a desire to explore more challenging roles, including negative characters and action, and plans to move towards OTT platforms for broader career opportunities.
title: Anjali Tatrari talks about exploring new characters after Vanshaj

description: Finance and education minister Atishi has been chosen as the new leader of AAP's legislative party, making her Delhi's eighth chief minister. Outgoing CM Arvind Kejriwal resigned following his release from jail. Atishi will lead until the assembly elections scheduled for February 2025, continuing Kejriwal's vision for Delhi.
title: Delhi gets its 3rd woman CM as Arvind Kejriwal hands charge to Atishi

description: Microsoft disclosed that a video falsely alleging Kamala Harris was involved in a hit-and-run is Russian propaganda. The video, shared by a fabricated news channel, seeks to influence US public opinion ahead of the presidential election. This demonstrates continued foreign efforts to manipulate American political views.
title: Fake Kamala hit-and-run story work of Russian group: Microsoft

description: Rahul Dravid's stellar performances against Australia, especially his 233 and unbeaten 72 in the 2003 Adelaide Test, highlight his resilience and technique. These innings were pivotal in India's historic victory on Australian soil. Dravid's ability to perform under pressure earned him great respect from Australian players and fans alike. The match is often remembered for Dravid's remarkable batting and India's historic victory.
title: When Dravid notched up one of the greatest performances by an Indian

description: David Lochridge, a former OceanGate employee, testified that the Titan submersible tragedy might have been avoided if his safety warnings had been investigated. He expressed disappointment with OSHA's lack of action. ​The Titan submersible disappeared on 18 June 2023, after losing communication with its support ship following its descent about 400 miles off the coast of Newfoundland, Canada.
title: Titan submersible tragedy could have been averted? Key employee's big claim

description: Shreyas Iyer's hopes of returning to India's Test cricket team are fading after a lackluster showing in the Duleep Trophy. With young talents like Sarfaraz Khan and Dhruv Jurel rising, Iyer's place is uncertain. A BCCI official cited concerns over his shot selection, casting doubt on his participation in upcoming tours.
title: BCCI drops a bombshell on Shreyas Iyer, says ...

description: The opposition INDIA bloc, comprising Congress, DMK, and communist parties, has declared a bandh in Puducherry on Wednesday to protest against the AINRC-BJP government's increased power tariffs. They argue that pre-paid meters and privatizing power distribution will harm farmers and result in unfair pricing. Former chief minister V Narayanasamy warned of further protests if demands are not met.
title: Why INDIA bloc has called for bandh in Puducherry

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi urged citizens to vote in large numbers as the first phase of Jammu and Kashmir assembly elections began. He particularly called upon young and first-time voters to participate. This election marks a significant milestone, being the first since the region's special status was revoked in 2019, with heightened security measures.
title: 'Strengthen festival of democracy': PM Modi's message to voters in J&K

description: Lieutenant Governor V K Saxena announced the resumption of land mutation based on inheritance for agricultural land in over 174 urban villages in Delhi. The process begins with camps set up in villages starting Friday. This decision impacts lakhs of residents who were denied this right since 2010 due to urbanization.
title: Delhi LG: Mutation of land in urban villages open, move to benefit lakhs

description: Bangladesh's interim government announced that former Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina is residing in India after her diplomatic passport was revoked. Her attempts to seek asylum elsewhere have been unsuccessful. Additionally, the government has granted magistracy powers to army officers for two months due to slow progress in improving law and order.
title: Dhaka on Hasina's stay in Delhi: 'Everything doesn't go by law'

description: Israeli operatives secretly placed explosives in pagers used by Hezbollah, leading to an attack that killed at least nine people and injured over 2,800 across Lebanon. The devices were triggered remotely through a coded message. This operation marks a significant intelligence failure for Hezbollah, which has vowed retaliation against Israel.
title: How Israel turned everyday pagers into deadly weapons against Hezbollah
Trans identity no ground to deny admission: Madras HC

description: The Supreme Court has annulled criminal proceedings against 30 Army personnel implicated in a failed operation that killed 13 civilians in Nagaland's Mon district in 2021. The court highlighted that the Centre had refused to provide the necessary sanction under Section 6 of the Armed Forces (Special Powers) Act, making the FIR unsustainable.
title: Botched Naga op: SC closes criminal cases against 30 Armymen

description: The Supreme Court has mandated that all state governments cease demolition activities until October 1 unless approved by the court. Highlighting concerns over the misuse of bulldozers as punitive measures, the court stressed the need for judicial oversight. Demolitions are permitted only for unauthorized constructions on public land.
title: SC halts bulldozer action without its nod till October 1

description: Congress's manifesto for the upcoming J&K elections omits any mention of Article 370, a notable shift from its earlier stance against its abrogation. Instead, the party emphasizes securing statehood for J&K. Meanwhile, ally National Conference pledges to restore Article 370 and facilitate the dignified return of Kashmiri pandits.
title: Congress manifesto silent on Article 370 restoration
Donald Trump says he will meet PM Modi next week

description: Rohit Sharma's Indian cricket team is set to begin a demanding Test schedule against Bangladesh in Chennai. Strategies are in place to manage the workload of key bowlers like Jasprit Bumrah and Mohammed Siraj. After facing Bangladesh, India will play New Zealand at home before heading to Australia for a five-match Test series.
title: 'We have some plans...': Rohit Sharma on bowlers' workload management

description: Dooru in Anantnag district, renowned for its literary heritage, is now politically significant as J&K prepares for assembly elections after a decade. AICC general secretary Ghulam Ahmad Mir of the NC-Congress alliance faces competition from PDP's Mohammad Ashraf Malik and Independents. The increased electorate of 116,749 voters may impact the election outcome.
title: Land of poets and storytellers gets ready to turn over a new leaf

description: Head coach Gautam Gambhir will lead Team India in his first Test assignment against Bangladesh after a difficult ODI series loss to Sri Lanka. The squad, with new bowling coach Morne Morkel, is training in Chennai. Rohit Sharma stresses the significance of mutual understanding between coaches and players as they gear up for the World Test Championship.
title: 'I know Gambhir...': Rohit on his understanding with India head coach

description: Finance and education minister Atishi has been chosen as the new leader of AAP's legislative party, making her Delhi's eighth chief minister. Outgoing CM Arvind Kejriwal resigned following his release from jail. Atishi will lead until the assembly elections scheduled for February 2025, continuing Kejriwal's vision for Delhi.
title: Delhi gets its 3rd woman CM as Arvind Kejriwal hands charge to Atishi

description: Isro's Gaganyaan mission progresses with a temporary ground station at Australia's Cocos Islands. The Australian Space Agency collaborates for tracking and emergency support. Joint satellite projects and climate initiatives are underway, reflecting deepening space cooperation between India and Australia.
title: Gaganyaan tracking station site finalised at Cocos Islands

description: Indian filmmaker Soham Shah has filed a lawsuit against Netflix and Squid Game creator Hwang Dong-hyuk, alleging plagiarism of his 2009 film Luck. Shah claims the concept of a deadly competition with increasing prize money was copied. Netflix and Hwang deny the allegations, asserting that any similarities are coincidental.
title: Netflix responds to Luck director's claim that Squid Games is his movie's copy

description: IBM has further expanded its FinOps portfolio by acquiring Kubecost, a leading startup in Kubernetes cost management. This acquisition follows IBM's significant investment in Apptio in 2023. Kubecost's technology helps organizations monitor and optimize their Kubernetes clusters, aligning with IBM’s strategy to offer comprehensive IT solutions to enterprises.
title: IBM acquires Kubecost, cost optimisation startup with Indian-origin co-founder
